args:
As Cleo and Lathna enjoy a festival outing, they
spy lanterns mysteriously flowing backwards up
the river. The sight causes Lathna to suddenly
cast an unknown spell, turning the lanterns into
zombies. The pair work together to fight off the
incoming tide of undead assailants.
Phew. That should about do it for all of\nthe yukata fitting I was asked to handle.

This year's festival in Quinbell looks as
though it will be quite popular. No doubt
the Halidom will be quiet as a result.
...Hm?
Wish they hadn't left me to watch the\nplace... I wanted to go to the festival.
Is that Lathna? Ah, if I recall, Curran and\nHeinwald did depart on sudden business\nthis morning.
Oh well. I'm sure I'd only be a bother if I\nasked someone else to take me.
It's okay. I know how to grin and bear\nthings. I'm fine being by myself.
But...I really did want to wear a yukata\nagain.
Worry not, Lathna. You need not ＂grin and\nbear＂ a thing today. Let's get you into a\nyukata!
Yes, that's right. And if it's a yukata you\nwant, I'm happy to dress you in one! Let's\nget you taken care of. The festival awaits!
...And now somehow I'm at the festival.
Lathnaaa! Look, I bought us some cotton\ncandy from one of the stalls.
Don't be bashful. Have as much as you'd\nlike. Do you need something to drink?
It's okay. I'll just snack for now. *munch*
Delighted to hear it! As long as you're\nhappy, I'm happy.
If there's anything else you'd like to do,\njust let me know. I want you to enjoy the\nfestival as much as possible.
(I know Cleo has a reputation for being\na nice person who always takes care of\neverybody...)
(But what made her so suddenly decide to\nbring me here?)
Um... Isn't it a bother, Cleo? For you\nto be babysitting me like this, I mean.
Not in the slightest. I wanted to see\nyou smile, so I'm doing this of my own\nvolition.

Please, just enjoy yourself. I may not
be exactly what you're looking for as a
substitute for Curran and Heinwald, but
I hope I'll suffice while they're away.
No, you're great... Thank you. Um, then\nif it's okay, I think I'd like to go see the\nlantern ceremony on the river.
I went there with Curran and them before.\nIt was really pretty.

That event certainly is a show-stopper,
isn't it? It's just like in its home country,
Hinomoto, where lanterns are set afloat on
the river to comfort the souls of the dead.
I myself wanted to see it at least once\nas well. Let's be on our way, shall we?
Moreso even than I had heard. Now,\nlet's release a lantern of our own.

Yeah. Curran showed me how to do it last
time. You fill your mind with thoughts of
someone who has died, and then you let
it go.
So I remember my mom and dad...
Um... Why're those people making a fuss?
Something must have happened.\nLet's go check it out.
The lanterns are flowing back up the river!\nWhat in the world is happening?
I don't know...but I've got a bad feeling\nabout this.
Ulthar, what's wrong? Are you sensing\nsomething with the lanterns?
Lost children of the soil, soaring from the\ndepths of twilight black! Gather at the\nguidance of the emissary, and obey Him!

Sacrifices unto Him, wandering lost
betwixt here and Beyond: revel in
newfound depravity and feast upon
the ignorance of humanity.
Huh? What in the world did I just—agh!
The spell you just cast turned the\nlanterns into...zombies?!
The monsters... They're attacking everyone.\nMaybe the scary thing inside me is\nrunning wild again?
No... No! Are people going to get hurt\nagain because of me?!
Calm yourself, Lathna. We need to get\naway from here, and quickly!
We'll talk after. You stay behind me.\nI'll use my magic to clear a path!
Begone, foul creatures of the night!
There's our opening.\nLet's get out of here while we can!
What?! More of them?! So relentless...
Once we've made our escape, we'll meet\nup with the others from the Halidom\nattending the festival! Understood?
